    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2009-06-16</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2009-08-13T16:01:56Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Broadband Internet Fairness Act - Makes it unlawful for major broadband Internet service providers to offer volume usage service plans imposing rates, terms, and conditions that are unjust, unreasonable, or unreasonably discriminatory. Treats a violation as an unfair or deceptive act or practice under the Federal Trade Commission Act. </p> <p>Requires major broadband Internet service providers offering or proposing to offer volume usage plans to file a service plan analysis with the Federal Trade Commission (FTC). </p> <p>Requires the FTC to enforce this Act. </p> <p>Defines &quot;major broadband Internet service provider&quot; as a broadband Internet service provider that, directly or through an affiliate, provides broadband Internet service to 2 million or more subscribers.</p> <p>Defines &quot;volume usage service plan&quot; as any choice of service offerings to a residential consumer that includes two or more different sets of rates, terms, or conditions directly or indirectly based on the amount of data transmitted to or from the consumer within a fixed period of time.</p> <p>Includes nonprofit organizations or higher education institutions in the term &quot;residential consumer.&quot;</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>Broadband Internet Fairness Act</title>
